iography.Will be of interest to students and scholars of several canonical early modern authors.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish poetryyEarly modern, 1500-1700xAppreciationxHistory. 0aEnglish poetryyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 4aShakespeare 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aAfterlife.  aDonne.  aGeorge Herbert.  aRobert Greene.  aSidney.  aSpenser.  aWalton.  abiography.  areception.  aself-fashioning.1 aChaghafi, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614496640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526144966423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526144966/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles